<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; HUNTINGTON HOSPITAL TO LAY OFF 25 EMPLOYEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huntington Memorial Hospital will lay off about 25 employees from its 
3,000-member staff this week in another sign of trouble for San Gabriel Valley 
health providers. 
</P>
<P>
 None of the layoffs include nurses, spokeswoman Peg Kean said.The layoffs are 
necessary because of a decline in patient admissions, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, San Gabriel Valley Medical Center laid off 17 full-time and 34 
part-time employees from its staff of 881; the former Inter-Community Medical 
Center in Covina cut 50 full-time positions from its 1,100-member staff through 
a voluntary separation package, and 80 people accepted an early retirement 
package at Huntington.  
</P>
<P>
 In addition, Inter-Community Medical Center and Queen of the Valley Hospital 
in West Covina merged last April under the name Citrus Valley Health Partners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
