<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR PARENTS; LIBRARIES TARGET KIDS WITH FREE ACTIVITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The San Gabriel Valley's public libraries are offering free summer programs 
for children, which include everything from reading circles and storytelling to 
movies, baking and puppet shows. Contact your local library for additional 
information. 
</P>
<P>
 Altadena Library District: (818) 798-0834 
</P>
<P>
 Summer reading club features activities Mondays through Fridays at 3:30 p.m. 
The activities include: outdoor games (all ages), preschool story time with 
music and movies (ages 3 to 6), skits and improvisational theater (ages 7 and 
up), movies and snacks (all ages). 
</P>
<P>
 The "Dive Into a Good Book" contest runs through July 30. 
</P>
<P>
 Azusa City Library: (818) 334-0338 
</P>
<P>
 Storytelling takes place every Monday. Please call for times. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration is under way for the "Dive Into a Good Book" contest. 
</P>
<P>
 El Monte Branch, County Library: (818) 444-9506 
</P>
<P>
 This month, obstacle courses, live animal shows, storytelling and baking at 2 
p.m. every Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Irwindale City Library: (818) 962-5255 
</P>
<P>
 Through Aug. 26: Tuesdays and Thursdays, 10 a.m. to 11 a.m., reading group for 
preschoolers. 
</P>
<P>
 Monrovia Public Library: (818) 358-0174 
</P>
<P>
 The summer reading club is sponsoring the "Dive Into a Good Book" contest for 
children ages 3 to 14. Children can win prizes depending on how many books they 
read. 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena Public Library, Central Library: (818) 405-4046 
</P>
<P>
 This month, storytelling, arts and crafts, movies, puppet shows for infants, 
toddlers and preschoolers. Call for specific times and days. 
</P>
<P>
 August: Magician Bob Stone will perform. Call for specific times, days and 
locations. 
</P>
<P>
 Rosemead Public Library: (818) 573-5220 
</P>
<P>
 Storytelling, arts and crafts, puppet shows and more at 2 p.m. every Tuesday. 
Programs run about 45 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 San Dimas Branch, County Library: (909) 599-0060 
</P>
<P>
 Summer reading program through Wednesday encourages children to keep track of 
the books they read by filling out a card and moving a wall marker in the 
library. 
</P>
<P>
 San Gabriel Public Library: (818) 287-0761 
</P>
<P>
 Storytelling, arts and crafts, puppet shows and more on Fridays at 2 p.m. 
Programs run about 45 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Walnut Branch, County Library: (909) 595-0757 
</P>
<P>
 Registration is under way for the summer reading program. Participants must 
have read one book before registering. They will receive a bookmark and index 
card to keep track of the books they will read. Call for information about 
additional programs. 
