<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PALOS VERDES PENINSULA; SERVICE OF 2 BUS LINES TO BE CUT BACK 
IN TRIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF KASS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two bus lines serving the Palos Verdes Peninsula will be cut back during a 
four-month trial, starting Sept. 5. 
</P>
<P>
 Lines 443 and 445 will each make three morning trips and three evening trips 
weekdays until Dec. 30, when the Metropolitan Transportation Authority will 
re-evaluate the number of riders using the lines. 
</P>
<P>
 Previously, the lines made five stops in the morning and five in the evening, 
said Dennis Morefield, a spokesman for County Supervisor Dean Dana, whose 
district includes the peninsula. 
</P>
<P>
 The MTA made the decision to cut service last Wednesday in an attempt to deal 
with a projected $141-million budget deficit. JEFF KASS 
</P>
