<HEADLINE>
<P>
SALVATION MOUNTAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I am constantly amazed at the arrogance of the human race. What has led me 
to this conclusion once again is the man who has spent the last eight years of 
his life painting (or defacing) a desert mound with his "testimonial" that he 
calls Salvation Mountain ("Slab City Showdown: Artwork May be Bulldozed as an 
Environmental Hazard," July 11). 
</P>
<P>
 I wondered as I gazed at his photograph, standing in front of his art, at the 
vanity (one of the seven deadly sins) which must have devoured his soul whole. 
How could he, I thought, look at that large gaudy collection of crosses and 
Scripture in red and white paint and see it, actually experience it, as more 
beautiful than the natural rock formation in its scenic surroundings that it 
was? 
</P>
<P>
 Does he really feel his creative endeavors superior to God's? 
</P>
<P>
 ALISON L. WAGGNER 
</P>
<P>
 Culver City 
</P>
