<HEADLINE>
<P>
AMERICAN LEGION BASEBALL PLAYOFFS ; VERDUGO HILLS WINS ON SQUEEZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ben Malen's suicide squeeze with one out in the eighth inning scored Corby 
Foster in Verdugo Hills' 1-0 victory over Quartz Hill on Wednesday in a 
District 20 American Legion playoff game at Birmingham High in Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
 Quartz Hill (16-7), seeded No. 3, was the first team knocked out of the 
10-team, double-elimination tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 David Gantt (4-2) pitched a five-hitter for Verdugo Hills (16-7), striking out 
eight and walking one. Gantt, who recently graduated from Glendale High, 
pitched a perfect game last spring for the Dynamiters. 
</P>
<P>
 Verdugo Hills' David Boger had two hits. 
</P>
<P>
 In other District 20 playoff games: 
</P>
<P>
 Valley North 9, Newhall-Santa Clarita 2 -- Tony Montiel hit a two-run home run 
and Bryan LaCour was three for six with three RBIs, leading Valley North to an 
upset of the No. 2-seeded team at Burroughs High in Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
 Montiel's homer broke a 1-1 tie in the top of the fifth. LaCour drove in three 
runs with a bases-loaded double in the seventh inning. Rod Daryabigi also added 
two hits for Valley North (15-8). 
</P>
<P>
 Jim DeBiase (5-1) picked up the victory by pitching seven innings. He gave up 
one run on seven hits and struck out six. 
</P>
<P>
 Aaron Dean hit his seventh home run for Newhall-Santa Clarita (17-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Encino 7, Van Nuys West 1 -- Barry Matthews scattered seven hits in 7 1/3 
innings for Encino at Birmingham High. The loss eliminated Van Nuys West 
(13-10). 
</P>
<P>
 Matthews, a right-hander who will be a junior at Crespi, gave up one earned 
run and one walk. He struck out five. Jon Cuccias pitched the final 1 2/3 
innings for Encino (17-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Encino put the game away with six runs on five singles in the bottom of the 
third inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Encino right fielder Ray Munoz had three of his team's eight hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills West 13, Antelope Valley South 12 -- A game between teams known 
for offense and not for pitching was high-scoring, as expected. 
</P>
<P>
 Unexpected, though, was top-seeded Antelope Valley South being upset at 
Burroughs High. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills West (16-7) will face Van Nuys East in a winners' bracket game 
at 4:30 p.m. today at Burroughs. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley South (18-4) drops into an elimination game against Encino at 
1 p.m. at Birmingham. 
</P>
<P>
 In today's other matchups, Verdugo Hills will meet Newhall-Santa Clarita at 10 
a.m. at Birmingham, and Sun Valley will face Valley North at 1 p.m. at 
Burroughs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
