<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOBEL RECIPIENTS CALL FOR DISSIDENT'S RELEASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Soviet leader Mikhail S. Gorbachev and the exiled Tibetan leader, the 
Dalai Lama, were among 14 Nobel Peace Prize recipients calling Wednesday for 
the release of Myanmar's pro-democracy dissident, Aung San Suu Kyi, at the 
start of her sixth year under house arrest. 
</P>
<P>
 The 49-year-old political prisoner, who has steadily gained support while 
waiting for the military junta to restore democracy, was herself awarded the 
Nobel Peace Prize in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
