<P>
 USAir Ground Workers Choose Union: The International Assn. of Machinists and 
Aerospace Workers bested the United Steelworkers of America for the chance to 
represent the nearly 8,000 workers who handle baggage and cargo for the 
Arlington, Va.-based airline, the National Mediation Board said. The board 
allows two working days for any allegation of election interference to be 
filed. If no such claim is filed by 5 p.m. Friday, the panel will certify the 
Machinists as the collective bargaining agent for the employees, who have not 
had union representation since 1990. The Teamsters lost the right to represent 
the workers a year after USAir and Piedmont Aviation merged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
