<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: ALLERGAN POSTS $23.5-MILLION PROFIT IN 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Allergan Inc., an Irvine manufacturer of health care products, reported a 
second-quarter profit of $23.5 million, or 37 cents a share. That compared to 
earnings of $24.6 million, or 37 cents a share, for the same period a year 
earlier, which included earnings of $1.2 million from discontinued 
operations.Sales were 8% higher -- $224.7 million, up from $207.9 million. For 
the first six months of 1994, the company posted a profit of $45.7 million, or 
72 cents a share. That compared to a profit of $48.3 million, or 72 cents a 
share, for the same period a year earlier, when the company had $2.6 million in 
earnings from discontinued operations. Six-month sales rose 6% to $434.8 
million from $410.7 million. 
</P>
