<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: NORTH HILLS; $25,000 
OFFERED IN DEATH OF WOMAN HIT IN CROSS-FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles City Council posted a $25,000 reward Tuesday for tips leading 
to the arrest and conviction of whoever killed a woman caught in a June 11 
cross-fire in North Hills involving a drug dealer.  
</P>
<P>
 Renee Milagros Hurtado, 21, was outside a liquor store when two stray bullets 
hit her.They just missed her daughter, who was in her mother's arms.  
</P>
<P>
 "Hopefully, this reward will stop a killer from killing again," said 
Councilman Joel Wachs. 
</P>
<P>
 Police, who are looking for a neighborhood drug dealer known as "Little Man," 
asked for a reward because they believe he might flee the area.  
</P>
<P>
 According to investigators, the assailant began firing at a man hiding behind 
a car that Hurtado and her sister-in-law had taken to the store. Hurtado, who 
was hit in the chest, died minutes later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
