<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: CERRITOS; MOTORIST 
STOPS TO OFFER AID, IS KILLED BY HIT-RUN DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Paramount man who got out of his car to help friends whose vehicle had 
broken down was killed Wednesday in a hit-and-run crash, a Highway Patrol 
officer said.  
</P>
<P>
 Javier Monje, 24, stopped alongside the northbound San Gabriel River Freeway 
near Del Amo Boulevard about 2 a.m., said California Highway Patrol Officer 
Bill Dance.A few minutes later, a maroon or dark red Volkswagen "bug" drifted 
onto the shoulder and hit Monje, Dance said.  
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the Volkswagen continued northbound and was last seen near Rose 
Hills Road. The right headlight of the subcompact car was broken and there was 
damage to the right front, Dance said.  
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information about the driver or the whereabouts of the damaged 
Volkswagen is asked to call the Santa Fe Springs CHP office, (310) 868-0503, 
during business hours, or (213) 669-4472 anytime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
