<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; RAPE 
SUSPECT SEIZED AFTER WOMAN SEES HIM DRIVE BY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A suspected rapist was arrested Wednesday after the alleged victim saw the man 
drive by as she was being interviewed by police, who chased him down.  
</P>
<P>
 "Officers were talking to the victim when she pointed to a passing car and 
said, 'That's the guy,' " said Los Angeles Police Sgt. Robert Courtland of the 
Rampart Division. 
</P>
<P>
 The officers jumped into their patrol car and chased the blue Datsun 280-Z out 
of the Westlake neighborhood, where the rape allegedly occurred, and onto the 
southbound Hollywood Freeway about 11 a.m., Courtland said. The pursuit 
continued south toward Downtown, then north on the Harbor Freeway toward 
Pasadena, the sergeant said.  
</P>
<P>
 The Datsun exited the freeway near Dodger Stadium and was stopped by officers 
near Figueroa Street and Cypress Avenue, he said.  
</P>
<P>
 The suspect, whose name was not released, was arrested without incident and 
booked on suspicion of rape, Courtland said. 
</P>
