ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / NORTH: ANAHEIM; ALZHEIMER'S PATIENT MISSING FOR 2 WEEKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are looking for a 65-year-old Alzheimer's patient who has been missing 
two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
 Teodoro Carreon of San Elizario, Tex., was last seen July 4 near Walnut Street 
and Katella Avenue, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police describe Carreon as a Latino, 5 feet, 4 inches tall and 150 pounds with 
receding gray hair. He was wearing a long-sleeved navy blue dress shirt and 
navy blue slacks. Carreon has a graying mustache and a scar on the left side of 
his face. 
</P>
<P>
 Police ask anyone with information to call (714) 254-1900. 
