<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / NORTH: BREA; MAGNITUDE 2.5 QUAKE LARGELY UNNOTICED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAIME ABDO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An earthquake shook North County at 3:28 p.m. Wednesday, but with a magnitude 
of about 2.5, it went mostly unnoticed. 
</P>
<P>
 The shaker was centered two miles east-southeast of Brea, said Caltech 
seismology lab spokesman Jay Aller. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea police said no damage was reported, and the department received only 
three or four calls from residents. 
</P>
<P>
 "They thought it was an explosion," said Martha Garza, who works in the 
records department. "They didn't know what it was." 
</P>
<P>
 No damage was reported in surrounding areas, police said. JAIME ABDO 
</P>
