11-YEAR-OLD BOY CRITICALLY INJURED IN AUTO COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 11-year-old boy was in critical but stable condition Wednesday after the 
car he was riding in was struck by a motorist who allegedly ran a red light, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Peter Anthony Rua, of Whittier, was being treated for head injuries and broken 
legs at UCI Medical Center in Orange, hospital officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Rua was a passenger in an auto that was struck when the driver of 
a Jeep ran a red light at Beach Boulevard and Warner Avenue about 10 p.m. 
Tuesday, police said. 
