</P>
<P>
 Day is being held in federal custody in Los Angeles without bail while a grand 
jury determines if there is enough evidence to indict him on one count of bank 
robbery, said Carol Levitsky, a spokeswoman for the U.S. attorney's office. Day 
could face up to 20 years in prison if he is convicted. 
