<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; RED CROSS TO TRAIN DISASTER 
VOLUNTEERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 East county residents interested in learning how to help their communities 
during emergencies are invited to a Red Cross meeting Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 At the meeting volunteers will learn how to join their local Disaster Action 
Team, which will teach them how to manage emergency shelters, assess 
disaster-related damage and help their neighbors during emergencies. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will be held at 7 p.m. at the East County Sheriff's Station, 2101 
Olsen Road in Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the Red Cross at the East Valley District office, 
582-8630. SARA CATANIA 
