<TEXT>
<P>
 Oxnard residents will once again be able to recycle used motor oil, latex 
paint, and other types of hazardous household waste under a new collection 
program starting today. 
</P>
<P>
 Since the Bailard Landfill Recyclable Household Hazardous Waste Station closed 
in January, Oxnard residents have had no way to safely dispose of such 
household wastes. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura Regional Sanitation District will operate a recycling station at 
the landfill, 4105 Gonzales Road, from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. on the second Thursday 
and Saturday of each month. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
