<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOPICS / BRIEFLY; ART: MULTIMEDIA PROJECT WINS JUROR'S AWARD AT FAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 West Los Angeles resident Roger Marshutz has received the California State 
Fair Juror's Award for his two-part multimedia work "Bruno: Ex-Gang Member" and 
"Oscar: Ex-Gang Member." 
</P>
<P>
 Marshutz's work, selected from 1,091 entries, are two 20-by-27-inch stucco 
covered boxes covered with graffiti.A photograph of Bruno and Oscar and a 
speaker hang in the front while a cassette tape player inside the box plays an 
interview with the former gang members. 
</P>
<P>
 The 64-year-old photographer said he was surprised he won. "It's not pretty 
art. It's not the kind of art you buy to hang over the couch. It makes a social 
statement. It's combative art, and a touchy subject," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The five Juror's Award winners received $500 and a Golden Bear trophy. Their 
work will be on display at the California State Fair in Sacramento through 
Sept. 5. 
</P>
