COMMUNITY NEWS: LOS ANGELES; SCHOOLS GAIN 5 DAYS IN 1994-95 CALENDAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Unified School District has added five days to its calendar in 
order to make up the time that campuses were closed after the Jan. 17 
earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 The school board voted unanimously on Monday to revise the 1994-95 school 
calendar so that the last day of class will be June 29 or July 1, depending on 
the schedule of each school. 
</P>
<P>
 Federal funding will pay the estimated $56.3 million in added costs. 
</P>
<P>
 The five days make up for the week that schools were closed for inspection 
after the Northridge earthquake. 
</P>
