 Third baseman Gary Gaetti was activated from the 15-day disabled list by the 
Kansas City Royals. . . . Enrique Calero, 22, filed a $15-million lawsuit 
against the Houston Astros and major league baseball, alleging he was cheated 
of his amateur status when he was lured into signing a professional contract 
and then released. 
