<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO RECORD FOR 9.96 IN 99.96 METERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT WHITE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tim Montgomery's junior world record of 9.96 seconds in the 100 meters, set in 
Odessa, Tex., in May, will not count after all. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S. Track and Field federation is withdrawing the time for certification 
by the International Amateur Athletic Federation after learning it came on a 
track four centimeters short. 
</P>
<P>
 The record, subject to IAAF ratification, will be 10.08, set by Obadele 
Thompson of Barbados in El Paso in April. 
</P>
<P>
 The 100-meter final in the IAAF World Junior Championships in Lisbon will be 
run today. MATT WHITE 
</P>
