<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: COMPTON; SCHOOL BUDGET REDUCES STAFF, INCREASES BOOKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The state administrator appointed to run the Compton Unified School District 
has approved a budget for next school year that cuts funds for paying employees 
but increases spending for books and supplies. 
</P>
<P>
 Administrator Jerome Harris also passed a five-year plan for the troubled 
district to repay nearly $20 million in state loans. The plan includes reducing 
staff by attrition or possibly by layoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 The 1994-95 budget increases spending for supplies by 1.5%, from $6.7 million 
to $6.8 million. The funds include $400,000 for new books. Funds for teacher 
salaries will decrease from $53.1 million to $51.4 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
