<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: NORWALK-LA MIRADA; SCHOOL BOARD ORDERED TO HOLD AN ELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Only a month after the Norwalk-La Mirada school board appointed a new member, 
the district has been ordered to hold an election Nov. 8. 
</P>
<P>
 School board member David H. Cosper's appointment was terminated last week 
after the Los Angeles County registrar's office determined that 719 valid 
signatures are on petitions calling for an election.Only 694 were needed. 
</P>
<P>
 Cosper, 43, replaced former school board member Jesse M. Luera, who was 
elected to the Norwalk City Council in April. Cosper had been in office for 
little more than a month when he stepped down.  
</P>
<P>
 He said he would not relinquish his seat without a fight. On Monday he was the 
first person to file his candidacy for the school board. Candidates have until 
Aug. 12 to file election documents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
